    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>  public static Path resolve(Path base, String... elements) {\n    return Arrays.stream(elements).map(Path::of).reduce(base, Path::resolve);\n  }\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 4647011,
      "reputation" : 45022,
      "user_id" : 3764965,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 94,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/7O3Pe.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Nikolas",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3764965/nikolas"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1739339704,
    "creation_date" : 1739339704,
    "answer_id" : 79432071,
    "question_id" : 412380,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<h3>Java 8</h3>\n<p>For combining multiple paths, there is an NIO package with <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/22/docs/api/java.base/java/nio/file/Path.html#resolve(java.lang.String)\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>Path#resolve(String)</code></a>:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>Path path = Path.of(&quot;/Users/user/Projects&quot;);\n\npath = path.resolve(&quot;work&quot;)\n           .resolve(&quot;bonk-app&quot;)\n           .resolve(&quot;docs&quot;);\n</code></pre>\n<blockquote>\n<p>/Users/user/Projects/work/bonk-app/docs</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>If you have the subpaths to be resolved in an array or any collection, you can use <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/22/docs//api/java.base/java/util/stream/Stream.html#reduce(java.util.function.BinaryOperator)\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>Stream#reduce</code></a>:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>Path path = Path.of(&quot;/Users/user/Projects&quot;);\nList&lt;String&gt; subpaths = Arrays.asList(&quot;work&quot;, &quot;bonk-app&quot;, &quot;docs&quot;);\n \npath = subpaths.stream()\n               .reduce(path, Path::resolve, (l,r) -&gt; r);\n</code></pre>\n<blockquote>\n<p>/Users/user/Projects/work/bonk-app/docs</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h3>Java 22</h3>\n<p>Java 22 offers two methods <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/22/docs/api/java.base/java/nio/file/Path.html#resolve(java.lang.String,java.lang.String...)\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>Path#resolve(String, String...)</code></a> and <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/22/docs/api/java.base/java/nio/file/Path.html#resolve(java.nio.file.Path,java.nio.file.Path...)\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>Path#resolve(Path, Path...)</code></a>. At the first glance, they look useful, though it depends on the source of subpaths.</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>Path path = Path.of(&quot;/Users/user/Projects&quot;);\n\npath = path.resolve(&quot;work&quot;, &quot;bonk-app&quot;, &quot;docs&quot;);\n</code></pre>\n<blockquote>\n<p>/Users/user/Projects/work/bonk-app/docs</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Anyway, it is good to know there is this option.</p>\n"
  } ],
